subSubSection.paragraph:
CONSERVATION STATUS. — Following the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (
IUCN 2012
), the new species is here assessed as Vulnerable (VU D1) due to its restricted area of occupancy, in a single location so far known, and low number of individuals observed. However due to the inaccessibility of most limestone outcrops in the area, its population size is possibly larger.

